practitioner.about:
Dr. Anuvinda Subhra Santhosh is a General Dentist attached to the Department of Dentistry at the JBR, Mirdif Speciality Centre branches of Medcare Medical Centre. She completed her Bachelor in Dental Science (BDS) from the Rajiv Gandhi University of Health Sciences and Fellowship in Dental Surgery (General Dentistry) from Saveetha Dental College, Chennai, India.

Dr. Santhosh started her career as a General Dentist working at Asnan Dental Care in Kuwait and then at Dentalman after which, she did another stint at Asnan Dental Care before relocating to the UAE. Her expertise covers oral hygiene education, teeth scaling, root planing and curettage, endodontic procedures, restorative procedures (tooth-coloured fillings and sealants), teeth extractions, teeth replacement (fixed and removable prosthesis, crowns and bridges), paediatric dentistry, aesthetic procedures (including veneers, teeth whitening, depigmentation, and gingival contouring using a laser.

She has treated patients with conditions ranging from decayed teeth, toothaches, stained teeth and mal-aligned teeth to replacement of missing teeth. She is good with paediatric patients and also treats gum-related diseases.

In her spare time, Dr. Santhosh likes reading, listening to music and dancing. She speaks several languages including English, Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam and Tamil.
